BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ford-foundation-technology-fellow-digital-safety-security-2026@artifici
 alnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260630T094952Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260706
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260707
SUMMARY:Deadline: Technology Fellow: Digital Safety and Security
DESCRIPTION:The Ford Foundation seeks a two-year Technology Fellow for Digi
 tal Safety and Security to expand the foundation's ability to support gran
 tee digital safety and security. Civil society organizations face targeted
  information security threats yet many lack the resources and training to 
 maintain robust digital security. Reporting to the Director\, Office of th
 e Vice President for U.S. Programs\, the Fellow will identify field-buildi
 ng opportunities in the public-interest digital safety and security field\
 , work directly with program officers across US and global teams to integr
 ate digital security capacity into Ford's technical assistance programs\, 
 provide strategic support to high-risk grantees\, and assess strategic gap
 s in the ecosystem for safety and security providers. The Technology Fello
 ws Program is administered by Ford's Technology and Society Program and is
  designed to increase sociotechnical capacity within the Foundation. Requi
 rements include a minimum of 7 years' professional experience with media\,
  technology\, advocacy or policy organizations\; a baccalaureate degree or
  equivalent experience\; sophisticated knowledge of existing and emerging 
 technologies with a focus on surveillance technologies and organizational 
 digital safety and security\; and experience designing\, implementing or s
 upporting digital safety and security solutions in a complex global settin
 g. Hybrid role based in New York (three days per week in office) with appr
 oximately 10 to 20 percent domestic and international travel. Not eligible
  for visa sponsorship\; candidates must be authorized to work in the Unite
 d States. Submit both a resume and a cover letter to be considered.\n\nOrg
 anisation: Ford Foundation\nLocation: New York\, New York\, USA\nAward: US
 D 166\,000 to 170\,000 annual salary\, plus comprehensive benefits and ret
 irement contributions of up to 13%\nDuration: Two-year term-limited contra
 ct\n\nMore: https://fordfoundation.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/en-US/FordFoundat
 ionCareerPage/details/Technology-Fellow--Digital-Safety-and-Security_R1295
URL:https://fordfoundation.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/en-US/FordFoundationCareer
 Page/details/Technology-Fellow--Digital-Safety-and-Security_R1295
LOCATION:New York\, New York\, USA
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:techcongress-congressional-innovation-fellowship-2027@artificialnouveau
 .github.io
DTSTAMP:20260630T094952Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260626
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260627
SUMMARY:Deadline: TechCongress: Congressional Innovation Fellowship 2027 (S
 enior and Early-Career)
DESCRIPTION:TechCongress places technologists in the US Congress to build t
 echnology capacity among Members and Congressional staff\, where fewer tha
 n 3% of legislative staff have a technical background. For the January 202
 7 cohort it is recruiting up to twenty fellows (10 for Democratic offices\
 , 10 for Republican offices) across two tiers: the Senior Congressional In
 novation Fellowship (mid-career\, at least eight years of work or postgrad
 uate study) and the Congressional Innovation Fellowship (early-career\, tw
 o to six years of experience\, including a recently finished or projected-
 by-January-2027 graduate technical degree such as a Masters or PhD\; appli
 cants with seven years qualify for an intermediate tier). Fellows choose a
  placement with a Member of Congress or a Congressional Committee\, report
  to a senior staffer (such as a Chief of Staff or Staff Director)\, and do
  work similar to other Congressional staff: researching tech policy (cyber
  and election security\, data and biometric privacy\, AI policy\, autonomo
 us vehicles\, health IT\, encryption\, disinformation)\, educating Members
  and staff\, writing legislation\, preparing Committee hearings\, markups 
 and investigations\, and building coalitions. No prior government experien
 ce is required\; the fellowship is first and foremost an educational exper
 ience. This year TechCongress also seeks at least two fellows from non-tra
 ditional verticals: climate (grid modernization\, clean energy\, NEPA refo
 rm)\, government innovation (govtech and digital benefits delivery\, civil
  service reform)\, and science\, research and innovation (NSF\, NIH\, DoE\
 , FDA reform\, clinical trials). Technical degrees or experience in engine
 ering\, development\, journalism\, scientific\, legal or government roles 
 are encouraged. TechCongress is a nonpartisan nonprofit incubated at the O
 pen Technology Institute at New America\; since 2016 it has sent 140 fello
 ws to Congress. Equal opportunity employer. Application deadline: 26 June 
 2026\, 5:59am (applicant's local timezone). Contact: aleena@techcongress.i
 o. Apply via the official application form.\n\nOrganisation: TechCongress\
 nLocation: Washington\, DC\, United States. Full-time\, in-person\; remote
  participation is not possible. Nonpartisan: fellows serve in both Democra
 tic and Republican offices.\nAward: Senior (mid-career) Fellows: USD 100\,
 600/year stipend. Early-career Fellows: USD 78\,000 annual-equivalent stip
 end (USD 6\,500/month). Plus health insurance supplement up to USD 425/mon
 th\, up to USD 2\,000 relocation to DC\, up to USD 2\,000 first-month shor
 t-term housing reimbursement\, up to USD 2\,000 official travel\, and a US
 D 500 professional-attire allowance. No application fee.\nDuration: Senior
  Fellows serve January to December 2027 (optional one-month extension). Ea
 rly-career Fellows serve January to October 2027.\n\nMore: https://techcon
 gress.forms.fm/january-2027-fellowship/forms/10111
URL:https://techcongress.forms.fm/january-2027-fellowship/forms/10111
LOCATION:Washington\, DC\, United States. Full-time\, in-person\; remote pa
 rticipation is not possible. Nonpartisan: fellows serve in both Democratic
  and Republican offices.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:blue-ridge-labs-founder-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260630T094952Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260503
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260504
SUMMARY:Deadline: Blue Ridge Labs Founder Fellowship 2026
DESCRIPTION:Founder fellowship for early-stage or new founders tackling pro
 blems in Robin Hood's five economic-mobility focus areas: Education\, Fina
 ncial Empowerment\, Health\, Housing\, and Hunger & Jobs. Applicants need 
 lived or learned experience with the challenges they propose to address. N
 o prototype or co-founder required at application. Approximately 25 founde
 rs advance from Phase 1 to Phase 2. Open to US applicants only\; no reloca
 tion expected for Phase 1\, but Phase 2 requires in-person time at the BRL
  Lab in Brooklyn. Apply via the Airtable application form linked from the 
 Robin Hood page\; submit an idea summary and background. Fellowship is ful
 ly funded by Robin Hood (no application fee\, no equity stake disclosed). 
 Note: this is a startup/entrepreneur-style fellowship rather than an arts/
 research fellowship\; applicants should be building venture-track ideas ti
 ed to economic mobility outcomes.\n\nOrganisation: Robin Hood (via Blue Ri
 dge Labs venture studio)\nLocation: United States (Phase 1 virtual\; Phase
  2 in-person at BRL Lab in Brooklyn\, NYC)\nAward: $20\,000 stipend in Pha
 se 2 to support MVP development. No equity terms mentioned. Includes weekl
 y mentorship and coaching\, workshops on product\, growth and fundraising\
 , co-working space at BRL Lab Brooklyn\, access to the Design Insights Gro
 up (DIG) community for user testing\, and network introductions across tec
 h\, philanthropy and policy.\nDuration: Phase 1 (Explore & Test): 6 to 8 w
 eeks\, June to July 2026\, virtual-first. Phase 2 (Build MVP): 10 to 12 we
 eks\, September to November 2026\, in-person Brooklyn.\n\nMore: https://ro
 binhood.org/our-work/blue-ridge-labs/founder-fellowship/
URL:https://robinhood.org/our-work/blue-ridge-labs/founder-fellowship/
LOCATION:United States (Phase 1 virtual\; Phase 2 in-person at BRL Lab in B
 rooklyn\, NYC)
END:VEVENT
